5/25/84  forum request: make_public, mp

Syntax:  mp {-control_arg}


Function: opens the current meeting to public participation.


Control arguments:
-chairman, -cm
   Gives chairman access to the public.  This control argument may only be
    used on version 2 meetings.
-read_only, -ro
   Allows the public to read transactions, but not enter them.


Access required:
Only the chairman may use this request on version 1 meetings.
For version 2 meetings, either modify permission on the
containing directory, or chairman access to the meeting is required.


Notes:
-read_only and -chairman may not both be specified.
